&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Airtable is the no-code app platform that empowers people closest to the work to accelerate their most critical business processes. More than 500,000 organizations, including 80% of the Fortune 100, rely on Airtable to transform how work gets done.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a results-oriented People Analytics Lead who is passionate about people data and improving employee experiences. You will own the People Teamâ€™s data strategy and will be instrumental in providing actionable insights to leadership to drive informed decisions and improve organizational effectiveness. Youâ€™ll work across engagement surveys, performance data, organizational health metrics, and talent analytics to unlock value from our data ecosystem. Youâ€™ll also be hands-on in building tools, dashboards, and frameworks that elevate how we scale as a global company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build Airtableâ€™s people analytics strategyâ€”defining core metrics, reporting sources, and scalable approaches to create compelling and actionable stories to drive insights and decision making across the people lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with HRBPs and business leaders to identify talent trends, surface risks, and generate insights across hiring, attrition, performance, internal mobility and employee engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a roadmap and prioritization process for continued development of our reporting and analytics capabilities across all people systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the process of conducting regular equal pay analyses to identify and address any gender or other statistically significant pay gaps, ensuring fair and equitable compensation practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and maintain dashboards, data models, and tools that transform complex people data into scalable,&amp;nbsp; intuitive and decision-ready insights.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and apply modern analytics tools, AI, and innovative techniques to expand the value of our insights and make reporting smarter, faster, and more impactful.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support key People programs (Talent Reviews/Calibrations, Engagement/Pulse Surveys, etc.) with subject matter expertise and data that drives alignment, clarity, and results. Bring rigor to methodology, analysis, and action planning support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in People Analytics, Data Science, HR Strategy, or related roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to build and scale analytics capabilities from scratchâ€”youâ€™re comfortable with ambiguity and know how to find the balance between structure and meeting the needs of the moment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with survey design and analytics, including methodology, interpretation, and driving action.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fluency in data analysis tools (e.g., SQL, Python, R, Tableau, Looker, or similar) and a strong sense of data integrity and storytelling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of People data and employee lifecycle processes (talent acquisition, talent development, rewards, workforce planning, DEI, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to influence with dataâ€”you know how to communicate complex insights in clear, compelling ways.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep curiosity and a builderâ€™s mindsetâ€”you experiment, iterate, and bring creative ideas to life.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Workday, Gem, Greenhouse and other people tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in high-growth or global tech environments is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Airtable is an equal opportunity employer. We embrace diversity and strive to create a workplace where everyone has an equal opportunity to thrive. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and perspectives. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status or any characteristic protected by applicable federal and state laws, regulations and ordinances. Learn more about your &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jAj2by1bto5g8Xqn9hWNAwPOMGNd_fM6/view?usp=sharing&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;EEO rights as an applicant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;VEVRAA-Federal Contractor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you have a medical condition, disability, or religious belief/practice which inhibits your ability to participate in any part of the application or interview process, please complete our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://airtable.com/shrq13fCV8h1sx2t8&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Accommodations Request Form&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;and let us know how we may assist you. Airtable is committed to participating in the interactive process and providing reasonable accommodations to qualified applicants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;#LI-remote&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation awarded to successful candidates will vary based on their work location, relevant skills, and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Our total compensation package also includes the opportunity to receive benefits, restricted stock units, and may include incentive compensation.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;To learn more about our comprehensive benefit offerings, please check out&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;slate-link selected&quot; href=&quot;https://airtable.com/careers/life-at-airtable&quot; data-slate-node=&quot;element&quot; data-slate-inline=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Life at Airtable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot; data-slate-fragment=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;For work locations in the San Francisco Bay Area, Seattle, New York City, and Los Angeles, the base salary range for this role is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$218,300&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$283,300 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;For all other work locations (including remote), the base salary range for this role is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$196,400&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$254,900 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please see our Privacy Notice for details regarding Airtableâ€™s collection and use of personal information relating to the application and recruitment process by clicking&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.airtable.com/company/personnel-privacy-notice&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1fKEf0G59m8RT2ZaOJyxoqQ3kW3oUaxhZ/view&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ðŸ”’ &lt;strong&gt;Stay Safe from Job Scams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;All official Airtable communication will come from an &lt;strong&gt;@airtable.com&lt;/strong&gt; email address. We will never ask you to share sensitive information or purchase equipment during the hiring process. If in doubt, contact us at &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:hr@airtable.com&quot;&gt;hr@airtable.com&lt;/a&gt;. Learn more about avoiding job scams &lt;a href=&quot;https://consumer.ftc.gov/consumer-alerts/2022/05/want-work-home-spot-scams-first&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Airtable is the no-code app platform that empowers people closest to the work to accelerate their most critical business processes. More than 500,000 organizations, including 80% of the Fortune 100, rely on Airtable to transform how work gets done.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Airtable People team is seeking a People Systems Engineer (Airtable Specialist) to design, build, and maintain the Airtable apps that power the employee experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Youâ€™ll own and evolve the People teamâ€™s most critical tools â€” including our performance management system, onboarding app, and people directory â€” and develop new Airtable-based solutions that put AI and automation at the center of their design. Your work will simplify workflows, improve data visibility, and help the People team operate more intelligently and efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While Airtable will be your primary platform, youâ€™ll also evaluate when other systems or tools may better serve a problem, taking a pragmatic, outcomes-first approach to how we build the People tech stack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sitting on the People team and partnering closely with IT and internal systems, youâ€™ll use Airtable, scripting, and platform-native AI capabilities to deliver intuitive, scalable, and high-impact tools that touch every Airtable employee.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Airtable Development &amp;amp; System Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, enhance, and maintain core People Airtable apps that support all aspects of the employee lifecycle, such as performance, onboarding, and employee data management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and architect new Airtable applications with AI and automation at the core, ensuring systems are intelligent, scalable, and adaptable as the company grows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use Airtable Interfaces, Automations, and Scripting to create clean, efficient, and data-rich user experiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Evolution &amp;amp; Enablement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain automations, integrations, and data flows between Airtable and tools like Greenhouse, Workday, Slack, and Google Workspace.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take a pragmatic approach to problem-solving,&amp;nbsp; evaluating and recommending alternative systems or tools when they better serve People team goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use scripting (JavaScript or Python) and APIs to connect systems and optimize recurring processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously monitor system performance, usability, and data accuracy,&amp;nbsp; iterating to meet evolving business needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with IT and cross-functional teams to align on architecture, data governance, and long-term tooling roadmap&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document technical logic and train stakeholders to use and maintain Airtable applications effectively. Promote Airtable best practices across the People team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Youâ€™re a systems-minded builder who designs with automation and intelligence in mind. You combine a product mindset with hands-on technical skill, and youâ€™re motivated by creating AI-driven tools that make work simpler, smarter, and more human for every employee.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years in systems engineering, internal tools development, or technical operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experienced in leveraging AI to enhance systems and workflows&amp;nbsp; : you experiment, tinker, and have experience using generative AI to build real solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience building advanced Airtable solutions using interfaces, automations, and scripting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skilled in scripting (JavaScript or Python) and integrating SaaS tools via APIs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pragmatic problem solver who evaluates the right system or tool for the job:&amp;nbsp; Airtable-first, but not Airtable-only.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with HR or People systems (e.g., Workday, Greenhouse, Slack, Google Workspace) preferred but not required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong data modeling and systems design abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and documentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, collaborative self-starter who thrives in fast-paced environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Airtable is an equal opportunity employer. We embrace diversity and strive to create a workplace where everyone has an equal opportunity to thrive. We welcome people of different backgrounds, experiences, abilities, and perspectives. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability, protected veteran status or any characteristic protected by applicable federal and state laws, regulations and ordinances. Learn more about your &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1jAj2by1bto5g8Xqn9hWNAwPOMGNd_fM6/view?usp=sharing&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;EEO rights as an applicant&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;VEVRAA-Federal Contractor&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;If you have a medical condition, disability, or religious belief/practice which inhibits your ability to participate in any part of the application or interview process, please complete our &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://airtable.com/shrq13fCV8h1sx2t8&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Accommodations Request Form&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;and let us know how we may assist you. Airtable is committed to participating in the interactive process and providing reasonable accommodations to qualified applicants.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400; font-size: 8pt; color: rgb(255, 255, 255);&quot;&gt;#LI-remote&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation awarded to successful candidates will vary based on their work location, relevant skills, and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Our total compensation package also includes the opportunity to receive benefits, restricted stock units, and may include incentive compensation.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;To learn more about our comprehensive benefit offerings, please check out&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;slate-link selected&quot; href=&quot;https://airtable.com/careers/life-at-airtable&quot; data-slate-node=&quot;element&quot; data-slate-inline=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;Life at Airtable&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-slate-node=&quot;text&quot; data-slate-fragment=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-leaf=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-slate-string=&quot;true&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;For work locations in the San Francisco Bay Area, Seattle, New York City, and Los Angeles, the base salary range for this role is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$149,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$232,300 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;For all other work locations (including remote), the base salary range for this role is:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-range&quot;&gt;&lt;span&gt;$134,000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;divider&quot;&gt;&amp;mdash;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;$209,600 USD&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Please see our Privacy Notice for details regarding Airtableâ€™s collection and use of personal information relating to the application and recruitment process by clicking&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class=&quot;c-link&quot; href=&quot;https://www.airtable.com/company/personnel-privacy-notice&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; data-stringify-link=&quot;https://drive.google.com/file/d/1fKEf0G59m8RT2ZaOJyxoqQ3kW3oUaxhZ/view&quot; data-sk=&quot;tooltip_parent&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ðŸ”’ &lt;strong&gt;Stay Safe from Job Scams&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;All official Airtable communication will come from an &lt;strong&gt;@airtable.com&lt;/strong&gt; email address. We will never ask you to share sensitive information or purchase equipment during the hiring process. If in doubt, contact us at &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:hr@airtable.com&quot;&gt;hr@airtable.com&lt;/a&gt;. Learn more about avoiding job scams &lt;a href=&quot;https://consumer.ftc.gov/consumer-alerts/2022/05/want-work-home-spot-scams-first&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Airtable is the no-code app platform that empowers people closest to the work to accelerate their most critical business processes. More than 500,000 organizations, including 80% of the Fortune 100, rely on Airtable to transform how work gets done.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Airtable is on a mission to democratize software creation.&lt;/strong&gt; Our platform is loved by people at more than 500,000 organizations, including 80% of the Fortune 100, because they can design and build powerful applications (without knowing how to code) that perfectly fit their needs and workflows. We believe that the future of software development is increasingly intelligent and interconnected, and we are looking for a visionary Product Manager to lead the charge in infusing AI, automation, and advanced integration capabilities deep into the core of the Airtable platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Product Manager for our Automation Platform, you will be responsible for crafting the vision, strategy, and roadmap to empower our users to build even smarter, more efficient, and seamlessly integrated applications. You will work at the intersection of cutting-edge AI technologies, powerful automation tools, and a rich ecosystem of integrations, fundamentally transforming how work gets done on Airtable (and beyond). This role requires a deep understanding of user needs in the context of AI-driven productivity, a passion for building intuitive and powerful platform capabilities, and the ability to collaborate effectively with world-class engineering, design, research, and go-to-market teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you&#39;ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Create 10x AI-Powered Solutions:&lt;/strong&gt; Pioneer revolutionary intelligent workflows and automations (think about agents and goals, not triggers) that fundamentally transform how organizations operate. Leverage cutting-edge AI to craft experiences that dramatically outperform traditional approaches, setting new standards for what&#39;s possible in workflow automation and intelligent data processing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive with a GM Mentality from Vision to Market:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the complete AI, automation, and integration strategy with full accountability for business outcomes. Lead end-to-end success by directing how these technologies create transformative value for customers and drive Airtable&#39;s growth. Develop compelling go-to-market strategies that communicate your innovations&#39; value, working closely with marketing and sales to ensure successful adoption. You&#39;ll connect every technical decision directly to measurable outcomes, leveraging AI tools yourself to accelerate processes and create competitive differentiation in the market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Immerse Yourself with Customers &amp;amp; Partners:&lt;/strong&gt; Engage directly with users to develop firsthand insights into their automation challenges. Conduct field research, run co-creation sessions, and build deep relationships that inform your product decisions and ensure solutions address real market needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Technical Exploration:&lt;/strong&gt; Build rapid prototypes and experimental features to validate new AI concepts before full development. Balance visionary thinking with pragmatic execution by gathering early user feedback, measuring impact, and iterating quickly to bring transformative capabilities to market.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build Platform &amp;amp; Ecosystem Capabilities:&lt;/strong&gt; Design AI and automation capabilities that are powerful, extensible, and integrate seamlessly with enterprise systems. Create opportunities for third-party developers to extend your intelligent workflow foundations while ensuring the overall health of the Airtable ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experienced Product Leader:&lt;/strong&gt; 8+ years of product management experience, with a significant portion focused on AI/ML-powered products, automation platforms, integration services, or developer platforms within a SaaS environment. Familiarity with Airtable, low-code/no-code platforms, and productivity tools is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI &amp;amp; Automation Enthusiast:&lt;/strong&gt; Deep understanding of AI/ML and LLMs, and their practical applications. Passionate about the potential of automation and intelligent systems to transform how people work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technically Astute:&lt;/strong&gt; Solid grasp of software development processes, API design, system architecture, and the technical underpinnings of AI/ML systems and integration technologies. Ability to engage in deep technical discussions with engineers and researchers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Thinker:&lt;/strong&gt; Proven ability to develop and articulate a clear product strategy, make tough prioritization decisions, and translate complex problems into actionable plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;User-Obsessed:&lt;/strong&gt; A genuine empathy for users and a commitment to building products that are not only powerful but also intuitive and delightful to use.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceptional Communicator &amp;amp; Collaborator:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to effectively influence and collaborate with diverse stakeholders across all levels of the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data-Driven &amp;amp; Analytical:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong analytical skills with experience in A/B testing, data analysis, and using data to inform product decisions and measure impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entrepreneurial Spirit:&lt;/strong&gt; A proactive, self-starter mentality with a track record of taking ownership, navigating ambiguity, and delivering impactful results in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bonus Points:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building or working with agent-based AI systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with enterprise integration patterns and iPaaS solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven success in launching 0-&amp;gt;1 products or significant new product areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
